<item>
            <title>[ZOOKEEPER-3878] Client connection fails if IPV6 is not enclosed in square brackets</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-3878</link>
                <project id="12310801" key="ZOOKEEPER">ZooKeeper</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Clients should be able to connect to ZooKeeper  with or without square bracket around IPV6 in connection string. &lt;br/&gt;
127:0:0:0:0:0:0:1:2181 and &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;127:0:0:0:0:0:0:1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;:2181 both should work.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-3106&quot; title=&quot;Zookeeper client supports IPv6 address and document the &amp;quot;IPV6 feature&amp;quot;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;ZOOKEEPER-3106&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;ZOOKEEPER-3106&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; fix connection with  127:0:0:0:0:0:0:1:2181 fails&lt;br/&gt;
I think we should support both  with or without square bracket around IPV6.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
